ICELANDIC INSTITUTE FOR INTELLIGENT MACHINES
R&D Programer/Analyst wanted

The Icelandic Institute for Intelligent Machines (IIIM) is seeking
professionals in software and/or engineering with excellent
programming skills.

IIIM is a recently-founded non-profit research organization In
Reykjavik,
Iceland, focusing on artificial intelligence and simulation. Funded by
government and industry, the Institute's charter is to significantly
speed up
advances in thes fields through innovative research and collaborations
with
academia and industry. Collaborators include Information Sciences
Institute
at USC (US), Strathclyde U. (Scotland), CCP, Ossur, and Reykjavik Univ.
(Iceland), CITEC and DFKI (Germany), and MIT (US).

Applicants should have a graduate degree in computer science,
engineering
or related discipline, and 5-10 years of industry experience, deep
knowledge
and experience in systems design, C++ coding and debugging, multi-
threading
and one or more interpreted languages. Familiarity with any of the
following
areas is a plus: Machine learning, pattern recognition (machine
vision, machine
hearing), realtime systems, multi-agent systems, large-scale and/or
high-
performance systems, knowledge representation, robotics,
dynamical systems, sensor fusion, signal processing.

Successful candidates will be given key roles and autonomy in the
design, development and delivery of advanced systems in the areas
of artificial intelligence and simulation.

Send Resume/CV and a short cover letter to: jobs@iiim.is



